The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                      SPORT BRIEFS
                  
	Mumbai: Suspended IPL chairman and commissioner Lalit Modi on Tuesday demanded the reconstitution of the BCCI disciplinary committee that has been set up to probe various charges of irregularities against him in the T20 tournament. Modi claimed that Chirayu Amin, the interim IPL chairman, had officially expressed his interest in buying stakes in a consortium that made a failed bid for the Pune franchise and as such his presence on the probe panel was unfortunate.        
	 Ranchi: Ranjib Biswal has been appointed the manager of the Indian team for the forthcoming tour of Sri Lanka beginning July 18. He had been manager of Team India in the World Twenty20 in the West Indies and recently concluded Asia Cup.        
	 Calcutta: Talented Kalighat batsman Sudeep Chatterjee has been adjudged CABs best U-19 cricketer for the last season. Abhishek Raman has been adjudged the best U-16 cricketer.     
	Other Winners: U-14: Sayan Mondal; University: Angel Nandi (RBU); School: Mustafa Shaikh (Shantipur Hindu HS); Junior: Soumen Chakraborty (Videocon School of Cricket); Sub-Junior: Puran Chand Singh Yadav (Howrah Sammilani)        
	 Calcutta: Pakistan women teams off-spinner Javeria Wadoods action has been found to be illegal, according to a media release by the ICC.        
	New Delhi: After Usain Bolt, Shelly-Ann Fraser, the womens Olympic gold medallist, has decided to the Commonwealth Games a miss this year.        
	 Johannesburg: The 800m world champion Caster Semenya was cleared to return to competitive athletics by the IAAF on Tuesday with immediate effect, ending an 11-month lay-off while she underwent gender verification tests.           
	 London: The upcoming English Premier League season will kick off at White Hart Lane with Tottenham Hotspur hosting Manchester City, it was announced on Tuesday.    
